  "time_ut": 1660450391,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b8f\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bcb\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "We will not accept ministerial posts",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "If an all-party government is formed, we will support it and not accept ministerial posts.",
        "Palani Digambaram, President of National Union of Workers and Nuwara Eliya District Member of Parliament said.",
        "He said this while speaking at a special meeting of the National Union of Workers held in Hutton.",
        "Tamil Progressive Alliance is working calmly considering the welfare of the people and future political activities.",
        "During the talks with the President, we have already announced that we will extend support from outside if an all-party government is formed.",
        "Economic problems of the people of the country can be solved only by working together of all the parties.",
        "The President has also announced that the country's economic situation will be worse for the next six months.",
        "And it is reported that the economic situation of the country will improve to some extent after another two years.",
        "In such a situation, accepting the responsibility of the ministry will not bring any development to the people.",
        "People will throw me out if I don't serve the people by accepting the post of minister for prestige.",
        "For me, I think it is appropriate to accept a ministerial responsibility after the election and serve the people."
      ],
